desc: Getting involved in holistic health and healing myself from endometriosis, the horrors of birth control, and so much more has opened my eyes to America constantly attempting to keep us in a sick cycle to always depend on pharmaceuticals. Health is solely for profit here and I wanted out. I spent 6 months in europe eating real, local food, walking every day, getting sunshine, drinking mineral water and it was the best Ive ever felt. Their reciepts were BPA FREE!! So I could touch them. They also view celiac disease as an actual disease so eating gluten free was a breeze. I never bloated after a meal and at this point I’m ready to move. I’ll be starting a blog soon on my wellness travels, creating guides so please let me know if you want to be notified when it goes live 💕 #europe #europeansummer #europeanhealth #traveltiktok #wellnesstravel #glutenfree #toxins #chemicals #bpa #syntheticfood #realfood #cleaneating #nongmofoods #italy #rome #wellness #holistichealth #movefromamerica #digitalnomadlife #movetoitaly #americaninitaly #digitalnomad #fyp #healthcare #healthy

desc: How I’ve traveled for 13 years 👇 (Save & share with someone who can relate!) Firstly, & honesty though I am very happy being single, especially after a painful breakup. I think it’s important to give yourself time to heal & work on fixing your own energy before taking on other peoples 🫶 Secondly, here’s HOW I’ve traveled so much: At 18 I went to Australia solo on a working holiday visa & worked for pretty much the whole time! Then visited some of Asia 🎉  During my university summers I went interrailling (thanks student overdraft) & worked a summer season in Greece as a waitress.  Post uni I worked 2 full time hour jobs (9-5 office & bar work evenings/ weekend), saved £3,500 & went away for 2.5 years.  I did this through budget backpacking, a working holiday visa in New Zealand for 2 years & volunteering for accom in Tonga & Hawaii.  Then I worked as a European Trip Leader for 2 years(thanks Covid)! I lead trips through a mix of 25 countries! I’d save during my trip leading seasons & use this money for personal travel in my months off between winter & summer. I also god discounts on Egypt & a trip around 6 African countries as I worked for a tour company! May 2021 I left the UK, started teaching English online, got a fully remote job & now I am a content creator, travel coach & social media strategist for brands.  I’ve also written an ebook which covers exactly how you can live this life too 🤩 So follow @daisystraveldiaries to learn how to travel full time & daily digital nomad tips! . . . #digitalnomadgirls #digitalnomad #fulltimetravel #solotravel #remoteworklife
hashtagNames: digitalnomadgirls, digitalnomad, fulltimetravel, solotravel, remoteworklife
stickersText: ['Don’t worry mum. I’m just doing a gap year while I’m 18 then I’ll settle down ', 'Daisy did not settle down. Daisy is now 31 & has been traveling ever since. Daisy is tragically single & falls in love with men as she travels, only to catch a flight to a new countries the next week. Daisy may never settle in the UK. SORRY MUM. ']

desc: 🚐Spend the day with us - Van life South Africa 🇿🇦  Today we woke up at a beautiful lakeside campsite called SwartVlei in Sedgefield 🙌 We made coffee, breakfast, cleaned the van and had a shower 🚿  Today we are off to explore some natural pools so we packed snacks and took a walk to the beachfront 🌊  Once at the beach we found a spot in the shade and setup our picnic- we tried the Harissa Hummus from Mama Alles 🥰 You just add water and stir! It was absolutely delicious guys, 10/10 😍😍 After our picnic we swam and explored the natural pools, we saw so many gosh and even a starfish ⭐️ Then it was time to head home 🚐  When we got back we filled our water tank, cleaned the dishes and cooked an early dinner 🍲  Tonight we had Moroccan Tagine from @Mama Alles  😍😍 You just add hot water to the bag or pot and in 10 minutes have a delicious meal 🙌  We ate dinner outside then had a call with family ♥️ Afterwards we drove to a spot to watch the sunset 🌅  Then it was time for snacks, netflix, brushing our teeth and heading to bed 😴  Thanks so much for watching ♥️🥰 If you are looking for super delicious convenient meals made with fresh ingredients check our @mama_alles 😍 Perfect healthy on the go meals for any occasion 🙌💗 - - - - #safyp🇿🇦 #🇿🇦 #viralsouthafrica #vanlifesouthafrica #dayinthelife #digitalnomad #travel
hashtagNames: safyp🇿🇦, 🇿🇦, viralsouthafrica, vanlifesouthafrica, dayinthelife, digitalnomad, travel
stickersText: ['VAN LIFE SOUTH AFRICA', 'Day in the life']

stickersText: ['Everyone talks about the great parts of solo travel but no one talks about how empty and lost you feel once you come back home.  You grow and change so quickly only to return back to a place where everything is the same. You no longer relate you people who are content in one spot. It’s hard to find joy in everyday life when you know you could be out there making even more memories and meeting more incredible people. Everything after just seems so minuscule.']

desc: 📍The Dead Sea. It’s incredibly cool, but it can actually be dangerous! When you swim here, remember it’s the lowest point on Earth, so the water is incredibly salty. It’s so salty, nothing can survive here. This means the water can be dangerous to ingest, and if you get it in your eyes it burns (trust me on this one). You CAN safely swim and float, but don’t splash or put your head under!! #travel #solotravel #digitalnomad #fulltimetravel #roadtrip #hikes #hostel #hosteleria

desc: Travelling full time can be so challenging. it to 10 years ']

desc: Europe's passport-free travel zone will be welcoming Croatia.  EU countries today voted on whether or not to admit the three nations into the so-called Schengen zone - a pact between countries to abolish border checks for those travelling between their territories. Croatia received unanimous support from the 26 Schengen member states. If you were using Croatia as a base to reset your Schengen day count you might have to find a different base.  And on the other hand it means more borderless travel for those that have secured a residency or citizenship in Schengen zone.  The world is becoming a smaller place.  #freedomofmovement #borderless #moveabroad #sovereignindividual #sovereigncitizen #croatia #schengencountries #schengenvisa #digitalnomad #nomadlife
hashtagNames: freedomofmovement, borderless, moveabroad, sovereignindividual, sovereigncitizen, croatia, schengencountries, schengenvisa, digitalnomad, nomadlife

desc: If I had a nickel for every time I mention I live in America, and someone brings up guns I would literally be rich. It’s honestly so sad that America has become synonymous with guns and I feel like people overseas think that we’re okay with it when the reality is, a lot of us feel helpless that politicians are putting profits over peoples’ lives.  Interestingly enough, living overseas has made me realize just how desensitized I’ve become to the rampant gun violence present in America and the fact that we’re one of the only countries in the world dealing with this very solvable issue. #digitalnomad #usa #uk #foryou #blackgirltravel

desc: Working as a digital nomad in Antigua and Barbuda has the following benefits: •Easy internet access. With an internet speed fixed 20.95 Mbps and mobile 33.80 Mbps, you can work in any part of the world from Antigua & Barbuda, feeling at home or office. •Smooth visa application process. Applying for the Antigua & Barbuda digital nomad visa is fairly easy, and everything is done online. Moreover, you will have to wait only 14 days for an answer. •Tax exemption. As a digital nomad, you are exempt from ping income taxes in Antigua and Barbuda. •Warm climate. With a tropical savannah climate, Antigua & Barbuda has pleasing year-round weather. The best time to visit Antigua & Barbuda is November to April, when it is least rainy and hot. •Delicious cuisine. Antigua & Barbuda has become a food destination because of its fresh seafood, flavored dishes, and top-notch rum. This place is a haven for rum distilleries and sugar plantations. •Leisure activities. In Antigua & Barbuda, you can enjoy a variety of activities. Among the activities you can enjoy are exploring rainforests, swimming with stingrays, biking, kayaking, diving, snorkeling, sailing, and fishing. In addition, hiking, horseback riding, bird watching, and island safaris are among the things you can do on land. #antigua #antiguaandbarbuda #carribean #carribeantiktok #carribeanfood #carribeanmusic #carribeanlife #workremote #workremotely #remotework #remorejobs #remote #online #jobs #onlinejobs #digitalnomad #digitalnomadlife #digitalnomad #bobmarley #views #shirleyheights #steelpan #rasta #vibes #susnsey #views #view #goldenhour #visa #learntok #fyp #travel #trabeller #wanderlust #adventure #exlpore #island #holiday #destination

desc: Read the full story below 👇🏼  I saw Turkey working in a cafe here in Dahab and couldn’t stop thinking about him. 💭  After seeing him for the first time, I had to leave to travel around Egypt for 2 weeks. Still I couldn’t stop thinking about him.  At the time I was reading a men’s pickup book which teaches men how to attract women and ask them out. If I wasn’t reading this book at the time I’m not sure I would have done what I did next… 📖 I promised myself that when I got back to Dahab I would ask him out. So I went to the cafe, sat there pretending to write something, and actually got up twice to ask him out but people kept on walking in. 😅 My friends then came to give me a bit of moral support, but I couldn’t do it. So we got the receipt and I wrote a note with my number on it.  Then, just as we were leaving, he walked out and sat on the other side of the road. That was my chance. I didn’t feel satisfied writing my number on the receipt, so I walked up to him and very awkwardly and nervously asked him out.  😬  2 days later we went on our first date in the mountains here in Dahab, and the rest, you probably know 😊#love #relationships #travel #viral #trending #digitalnomad
hashtagNames: love, relationships, travel, viral, trending, digitalnomad

desc: The Future Workforce Alliance is proud to announce the first 3 signees of the European Charter for Digital Workplace Well-Being.  Lídia Pereira, Member of the European Parliament (EPP, PT) Dragos Pislaru, Member of the European Parliamnent (Renew, RO) Alex Agius Saliba, Member of the European Parliamnent (S&D, MT) This historic document aims to protect the mental health of remote & hybrid workers. There are four themes covered by the charter: (1) Life Beyond Work, (2) Social Connection, (3) Privacy & Trust, and (4) Digital Wellness. We are deeply grateful to all 3 MEPs for their leadership and support. Now we are urging more MEPs to support the call for solutions that will improve the experience of remote working for current and future generations. For more information follow the link in our bio. #workanywhere #remotework #workremotely #remoteworker #workandtravel #digitalnomad
hashtagNames: workanywhere, remotework, workremotely, remoteworker, workandtravel, digitalnomad

desc: Michael and Acacia (yeti.the.van) have been living full-time in "Yeti the Van" for over a year now. They're both originally from South Africa and have spent the majority of their first year in Yeti exploring their own country and region.  In this video, Michael and Acacia want to share a little bit about their story and why they chose to live full-time in a van.  In May 2021 they started their nomadic journey living in a small Suzuki SUV. This move was done for them to begin exploring and traveling but also for them to start saving up to be able to afford Yeti.  Michael and Acacia are professional videographers and photographers and find that their nomadic lifestyle has allowed their business to expand.  This video was brought to you by Orion by Up-Switch. It is a fully integrated Nintendo Switch Portable HD 11.6 inch IPS Monitor which is perfect for gaming on the road. desc: What’s a big life event Argentina does better than most countries?! WEDDINGS 💍👰💒 Imagine a massive dance party that goes to the early hours of the morning. The DJ is the soul of the event, and we’re not talking about some part-time DJ that plays songs from his iPhone. These are serious professionals that bring smoke machines, LED screens, lasers, and more.  🔎 So, how can you get on the invite list?! Thankfully, most Argentines enjoy hosting big weddings with lots of family and friends. Befriend a few locals during your time in Buenos Aires, and chances are you’ll be dancing until 4 a.m. during one of their big days.  (Or, who knows, maybe it’ll end up being your wedding 😉)  Would you add an Argentine wedding to your travel bucket list?!  #argentinewedding  #expatlife  #argentineculture  #moveabroad  #digitalnomadlife
hashtagNames: argentinewedding, expatlife, argentineculture, moveabroad, digitalnomadlife

desc: ✈️ MOST DURABLE TRAVEL ITEMS‼️ It is WILD that all of these items have stayed strong for the last four years of us backpacking all around the world. There’s something to be said about durability and things being worth the cost up front 🙌🏼  Osprey Fairview 55 Backpack: This is the GOAT of backpacking bags. I can’t believe it’s been literally around the world with us and is still like new. Forever obsessed! Gomez Compression Packing Cubes: Our absolute holy grail travel item it’s shocking we haven’t had to replace them.  Kanken Day Backpack: I actually bought this is Thailand in 2019 and it’s still in perfect shape. 10/10 best day bag to carry around cities. Amazon Universal Travel Adapter: This adaptor has been everywhere with us, even on domestic trips. It’s perfect to plug in multiple devices at once!  Eddie Bauer Raincoat: So durable and lightweight for travel - this jackets goes everywhere with me!  Rainleaf Microfiber Towel: This is the best travel towel and it barely takes up any space in your bag! desc: Auwal Masjid, The oldest mosque in South Africa.   #capetown #capetowntiktok #southafricantiktok #bokaap #digitalnomadlife
hashtagNames: capetown, capetowntiktok, southafricantiktok, bokaap, digitalnomadlife
stickersText: ['On the colorful streets of Bo Kaap is the oldest mosque in South Africa…', 'It is the first mosque to observe public prayers and is where Cape Muslim traditions and the Arabic-Afrikaans language were first taught.', 'It is a symbol for Muslims of the recognition of Islam and the freedom of slaves to worship.', 'While the first Iman, known as Tuan Guru, was a political prisoner he wrote the entire Quran from memory which is on display here.', 'You can still hear this call to prayer daily in Bo Kaap and it moves deep within your soul…', 'Alhamdulillah!  ']

desc: What started as a little escape from the hustle & bustle of General Luna in Siargao led to a love affair with the idyllic sanctuary of the north. Here are 4 reasons why you’ll fall for this enchanting paradise: 1- It has something magical & healing to it—the further north you go, the more you will see and feel it. Nature around here with oceanside roads are just captivating.  2- If you’re anything like me who embraces serene, local vibes, charming restaurants (yes, even with veggie options!), secluded beaches, and uncrowded surf breaks - the north is for you.  3- It’s a ‚everyone knows everyone kinda environment‘ so here you really have the chance to connect to a small, beautiful community. One thing that I just have to highlight is @kolekbibo, an NGO empowering local communities—check their beachfront restaurant, yoga and consider volunteering. 4- Amazing sunsets over the ocean (you don’t get that in the south!), whether you’re surfing into the golden hour or simply basking on the beach. 🤍 #TravelSiargao #SiargaoDiaries #Siargaoisland #siargao #Siargaovibes #SiargaoAdventures #filipino #filipinorelatable #filipinotiktok #Philippinesparadise #gophilippines #tropicalvibes #SurfingDestination #IslandLife #TravelInspiration #thatgirl #tropicalvibes #digitalnomadlife

desc: Quick introductions 😊 I’m Sarah, a digital nomad living in Buenos Aires, Argentina.  I’ve been here for 5+ years, and it’s been the absolute best experience of my life — follow along to learn why 👀    I met my now husband working at a ski resort in Colorado and, after falling in love in two short months, I moved to Argentina. (Yes, my friends & family thought I was nuts, but it worked out 😉)  Before moving to Argentina, I worked & traveled across several countries, so I have plenty of insight into living abroad.  And… I can now say without a shadow of a doubt: Buenos Aires is an INCREDIBLE place to be a digital nomad.  My hope is to inspire & empower other women who are interested in the digital nomad lifestyle with inside tips, resources, and reasons to start your journey in Buenos Aires. Because here’s the thing: you can absolutely do it! And you’re not alone.  Follow along if even the tiniest part of you is interested in taking your remote job abroad — and be prepared to fall in love with Buenos Aires ❤️ #femaletravelbloggers #solofemaletraveler #digitalnomadlife #workfromanywhere #fallinlove #buenosairestravel #argentinatravel
hashtagNames: femaletravelbloggers, solofemaletraveler, digitalnomadlife, workfromanywhere, fallinlove, buenosairestravel, argentinatravel, femaletravelbloggers, solofemaletraveler, digitalnomadlife, workfromanywhere, fallinlove, buenosairestravel, argentinatravel

desc: After 6 years in my apartment everyday started to feel the same. New decorations didnt help. Saging wasn’t enough lol. I found new hobbies trying to make time pass. Then I finally asked God to guide me, point me in the direction that I needed to go. I’m the only child so it’s normal for me to stay in my bubble, and figure things out on my own. This time I was truly stuck. Then one day, I started reflect on these past few years. I made myself a priority, I started taking solo vacations, received a job in aviation, got more passport stamps, and last month I asked myself what’s truly stopping me from leaving? I never felt like I fit in with certain spaces, and now I realize I wasn’t supposed to. After researching for days, sacrificing sleep, selling all my material things, and reaching out to others that dare to be different… IM MOVING TO MEXICO! Follow me on this journey to find a apartment! Link in bio for my YouTube ✨ & thank you @Shawnie🧚🏾 @Jasx ✨ Bougie Hippie Abroad  @Creator • Coach • Expat @Lynette Adkins for sharing your experiences moving abroad & never looking back! Follow & subscribe to them 💕 #digitalnomad #digitalnomadgirl #digitalnomadlife #mexico #playadelcarmen #tulum #atlanta #georgia #blackgirltiktok #blackgirlmagic
hashtagNames: , , , , digitalnomad, digitalnomadgirl, digitalnomadlife, mexico, playadelcarmen, tulum, atlanta, georgia, blackgirltiktok, blackgirlmagic
stickersText: ['POV: You Decide To Sell Everything & Move To Mexico \U0001f979✨']

desc: This might sound silly, but..  I was feeling restless and unproductive during my stay in General Luna in the south of Siargao. I sensed the need for a getaway, a place remote and serene, away from the hustle and bustle of the busy hub and social life. ✨ So, on a whim, I packed a small bag, strapped my surfboard onto my scooter, and headed north, all the way to the most northern point of Siargao Island. The 1.5-hour drive was filled with breathtaking scenery that only grew more beautiful as I ventured further. Along the way, I would pause, absorbing the incredible beauty that surrounded me, realizing that I was healing from something, anything. 🤍 When I arrived at my hotel, just a short walk from one of the most stunning, uncrowded beaches with crystal-clear waters, adorned by fishing boats and encircled by countless palm trees, I knew I had found my sanctuary. My days were spent either surfing alone, catching those perfect waves, or sharing the waves with just one other person. It was an incredible experience, feeling the power of the ocean and the freedom it brings. I dedicated time to building my website for @aryclub.official, finally ticking off substantial tasks while immersing myself in the beauty and tranquility of the surroundings. It goes without saying that I fell head over heels for the north of Siargao; there’s an undeniable magic in this area. The experience was a powerful reminder that sometimes, all it takes is a spontaneous journey to reconnect with ourselves and find solace in the beauty of nature. I feel a renewed sense of purpose and energy, ready to take on new challenges and continue the journey of reinventing myself. 🫶  If you’re ever in Siargao; you now know where to go 🦋 #SiargaoDiaries #surfergirl #digitalnomadlife  #surfinglife #reels #tropicalvibes #motivationalreel #inspirationalreel #healthandwellness #thatgirl #dailyhabit #Siargaoisland #siargao #Philippinesparadise #gophilippines #IslandLife #travelinspiration

desc: Replying to @sarabnmaxip  Finding and booking these repositioning cruises is actually a lot easier than I thought it would be. Using websites like the Royal Caribbean and other cruise liner websites you are actually able to search up there through the search bar. You can select your dates, select your locations and you can select repositioning transatlantic or transpacific to find the cruises that are the best for you at the price of under 800 under 500 and even cheaper.  This is really perfect for the digital nomad and their lifestyle full time travelers or people that are looking to see those destinations and make a crazy journey out of getting there rather than flying. desc: What it was like taking my daughter to a pediatrician in Egypt! My daughter developed a 102 degree fever during our second week in Egypt (teething). We called a doctor and they told us we could come immediately.  We arrived 15 minutes later and the doctor saw us within 10 minutes of our arrival.  It was a flat fee of $2.00 to see the doctor and he prescribed us a natural remedy to break her fever which cost $3.00 So basically,  $5.00 and 45 minutes later we were back at home taking care of the baby. Her fever was gone about an hour later. ✨ ✨ ✨If youd like more info on passive income and moving abroad  Text RISE to 470-354-0340 . #worldtravel #digitalnomad #locationindependent #fyp #fyppppppppppppppppppppppp #egypt #travelegypt #costaricaexpats #egyptexpats #singlemom #singlemomlife #digitalnomadlifestyle

desc: one of my favourite spots in Berlin 💃🏽 introducing the insider tip that is the riverside dance floor of Monbijou park.  during summer, there’s open-air dancing every single evening where anyone can get up and have a little boogey - anddd for a fee, you can also get professional a class before the open dancing begins.  the atmosphere is beautiful, the views of the river/ bode museum are wonderful and there’s so much fun and joie de vivre that it makes a greattt spot for people watching. ✨ 📌from the website, the current 2023 schedule goes like this:  ~ mondays: salsa (19.00-22.00) ~ tuesdays: standard & latin (19:00-22:00) ~ wednesdays: tango (18.00-22.00) ~ thursdays: salsa (19.00-22.00) ~ fridays: swing (17.00-22.00)  ~ saturdays: bachata (16.30-19.30) & latin (19.30-22.00) ~ sundays: swing (16.00-22.00) which would be your day? 🪩 . . . . . #thisisberlin #berlincity #berlinguide #berlinlife #localtips #authenticexperience #openairdance #freespirit #freedomlifestyle #createyourdreamlife #madeformore #slowtraveller #madetottravel #slowtravel #digitalnomadlifestyle #exploregermany #fulltimetraveller #womentravelsolo #solofemaletravel #berlinliving #berlinsummer #exploreberlin

stickersText: ['I’ve realized that working US hours in Europe is the best case scenario. I live a full day before the work day even begins. I can sightsee, I can explore, and after lunch I begin my work day. I work until 10-11p depending on the country, I take a break when my coworkers have lunch. I can go for a walk, take an hour to myself to make dinner or try a new restaurant. In the winter, it can be hard but the summers are euphoric. In the end it’s all worth it. ']

desc: two tickets to Britain’s oldest cinema please 🎟 there’s a reason why i prefer airbnbs over hotels, small local side alley restaurants to chains, living in old apartments rather than new builds or in this particular case on a visit to the cinema, going vintage rather than standard.  it’s because i love places that have stories to tell, to imagine the people that have passed through its doors, to feel its history, character and energy.  this here is considered to be the UK’s oldest cinema, first opening its doors in 1909 where it originally showed silent films with piano backing 😍.  tickets are pretty pricy at £25 each but if you’re also someone that enjoys more authentic experiences that are a little different, this cinema in London is one to watch (especially on a rainy day). 📍electric cinema, portobello, london  . . . . . #london #thisislondon #bestoflondon #itssolondon #portobello #londonuk #lifeinlondon #visitlondon #londondiaries #londonlove #nottinghill #electriccinema #vintagecinema #createyourdreamlife #createyourreality #madeformore #spiritualgrowthjourney #freedomlifestyle #slowtraveller #slowtravel #femalefounder #digitalnomadlifestyle #remotework #digitalnomadspirit #freespirit  #fulltimetraveller #solofemaletravel

desc: 🎶 the lyrics of this song are a love letter to berlin - presenting it as an ever evolving city that’s full of life and colour.  it celebrates its rebirth in the way that it has managed to attract people to it since its destruction in world war ii .. and the charm it has for anyone who visits. 🎶 it seems people have strong opinions about berlin … they either love it or they hate it. i believe i’ll forever be a lover of this capital and an encourager of others who want it to come and experience the city for themselves, especially at a deeper more authentic level 🫶🏽 as Leonardo da Vinci once said, “nothing can be loved or hated unless it is first understood.” if you have plans to visit berlin and want to get to know the more locally loved places and leave with more of a connection to the city, i’ve made a list of my favourite spots after 7 years of living here at the link in my bio 🥰✨  . . . . . #thisisberlin #berlincity #berlinguide #berlinlife #localtips #berlinlocal #localguide #authenticexperience #openairdance #freespirit #freedomlifestyle #createyourdreamlife #madeformore #slowtraveller #madetottravel #slowtravel #digitalnomadlifestyle #exploregermany #fulltimetraveller #womentravelsolo #solofemaletravel #berlinliving #berlinsummer

desc: I know this video will be kinda controversial considering what is happening atm with housing in Lisbon… but I’m just trying to share with you my honest budget to help others who might be wondering how much it costs to live in central Lisbon.  Alsoooo I’ve been living here for a year and a half now and sadly rent has gone really up so might not find something for this price, but some landlords are still asking for fair prices so don’t give up!  Last thing: I don’t have a very expensive lifestyle, I don’t party a lot anymore and I’ve been trying to eat out less ahah if you have any questions please leave me a comment :) #lisbon #livinginlisbon #freelancer #digitalnomadlifestyle

stickersText:
['“Beruntung banget bisa kerja remote”', '“Beruntung banget bisa hidup ala digital nomad”', '“Beruntung banget bisa keliling dunia di usia muda”', 'Funny if they think
I got it all by “luck”', 'Sebelum kuliah, gue ga pernah ngerasain ke luar negeri. Simply ya ga punya uang buat itu.', 'So, back in college, I worked hard to achieve my dream to travel the world for free.', 'I don’t have the money?
At least I have the brain. Something yg semua orang punya dan bisa dikembangin, diusahakan.', 'Berusaha ikut lomba/konferensi/research internasional biar bisa ke luar negeri. Keterima! Lolos!
But still, I don’t have enough money or get enough scholarships untuk cover semuanya', 'Gue nggak punya background business sama sekali. Dan sebagai anak semester 3 wkt itu gue harus pitching proposal & project gue untuk didanai di depan banyak bos besar multinational companies.', 'Akhirnya gue berusaha cari sponsorship sendiri ke perusahaan2 & lembaga2 tanpa ada yg ajarin gue.', 'Akhirnya selama gue kuliah, gue bisa pergi ke 10+ negara FOR FREE hasil dari sponsorship & scholarship yg gue usahakan tadi. Ke negara2 itu pun utamanya bukan untuk traveling tapi untuk mengharumkan nama Indonesia dg kemampuan gue.', 'Sejak itu gue semakin pengen menjelajahi dunia.
I wanna explore the world and be the global citizen!', 'And now I’m working remotely & adopt a digital nomad lifestyle. Sesuatu yg masih asing buat banyak org terutama di Indo.', 'Nope :)
Prestasi itu pun hasil kerja keras yg panjang. Itu pun apakah gue sekali langsung dapet kerja remote?

No. Ada ribuan rejections dan pengalaman pahit yg harus gue lewati.', 'Banyak yg kira semua hanya karna gue berprestasi “dari sananya”?', 'But what did I do?
I KEEP GOING', 'YOU WANT MY LIFE.

BUT DO YOU WANT MY PROCESS TOO??'], ['“LUCKY”']

desc: if you’re heading to Berlin on a weekend, it’s important to plan for Sundays a little more, as all shops etc are closed - but there’re plentyyy of things happening to enjoy.  this here is one of them, aka, Mauerpark, the place that turns into a mini-festival slash circus. Picture musicians making music in every corner, basketballers on the court, flea markets, food trucks and my favourite... a large open air karaoke that starts at 3pm where anyone can get up to sing with the encouragement from the crowd. 😍 what do you think? would you volunteer? 🎤😄 ____ if you’d like a list of the top 33 local experiences to have in Berlin like this one for your next trip - head to the link in my bio. i wish you a beauuutiful trip! ✨ . . . . . #thisisberlin #berlincity #berlinguide #berlinlife #localtips #berlinlocal #localguide #authenticexperience #openairdance #freespirit #freedomlifestyle #createyourdreamlife #madeformore #slowtraveller #madetottravel #slowtravel #digitalnomadlifestyle #exploregermany #fulltimetraveller #womentravelsolo #solofemaletravel #berlinliving #berlinsummer #mauerpark #mauerparkberlin

desc: Part ONE. Time to tell my story 👩🏼‍💻#digitalnomadlife #nomad #nomadgirl #digitalnomadlifestyle #travelstory #digitalnomadgirl #workfromanywhere
hashtagNames: digitalnomadlife, nomad, nomadgirl, digitalnomadlifestyle, travelstory, digitalnomadgirl, workfromanywhere
stickersText:
['My story of how I became a Digital Nomad (PART 1)', 'I got fired from my agency job in NYC while I was living paycheck to paycheck.

I couldn’t afford to live there without a job, but I felt SO burned & I really didn’t want another corporate job…', 'All I wanted was to TRAVEL but was broke. 
I sold my stuff, got my security deposit back from my apt, spent a month working odd jobs, and booked a 1-way ticket to THAILAND.', 'My original plan was to teach English but I ended up getting an amazing job editing a magazine instead!! 😎 (I NEVER would’ve been given that opportunity in NYC but in Thailand businesses need people with my skills!)', 'My career took off in Thailand! I made friends from all over the world, I lived in luxury on the 27th floor with a private gym and pool… my life was glamorous AF (& really f*ing fun). ', 'Then… there were 3 major tragedies at home 💔 I moved back to the US without a plan.  I tried to fit in, but living abroad had changed me. 

I didn’t know what I’d do next but I KNEW I wanted to keep my traveling lifestyle alive.', 'After a few months of serious soul searching, I landed a new job that was totally REMOTE while I was on a 2-week trip to Costa Rica. I cancelled my return flight home, and stayed with my laptop. 

My digital nomad life was born! ', 'Part 2!', 'Follow for Part 2!  👉🏻']

desc: when i shared the places i lived in my 20’s in a post last week, I had a lot of q’s asking how… and more importantly I noticed that there was perhaps a misconception that you need a lot of money to be able to do it, which (whilst helpful of course) definitely isn’t a must! Straight after university I left the UK for New York, with only small amount in the bank but a biggg desire to experience living everywhere i’d ever dreamed of before i’d have to ‘settle down’ in one stable job. and by either making money while abroad or finding ways to live there while spending almost nothing, i managed to moved to six countries throughout my entire 20’s. for the most part, it did mean living pretty minimally, but the experiences were anything but ✨🫶🏽 i would also like to add one thing though - if i was 20 again in this era right now, i would go straight to finding ways i can become a digital nomad to be able to travel freely long term whilst earning money online (which is what i do now too). BUT, if you just want to dip your toes into experiencing life somewhere else / make your first move solo (almost for free), then these are some great things that absolutely anyone can do, no matter who you are or how much money you have.  if you feel that pull to travel, you’ll find a way and i hope this post reaches some budding serial expats and offers some inspiration ✨ . . . . . #c#createyourdreamlifes#slowtravellerm#madetottravelf#freedomlifestylef#freedomlifel#lifejourneya#authenticexperiencel#localfindsh#hiddengemss#slowtravelf#founderstoryd#digitalnomadlifestyled#digitalnomadlife#f#freespiritf#fulltimetravellerw#womentravelsolos#solofemaletravel#m#madeformores#spiritualgrowthjourneys#selftruste#expatlifea#aupairlifea#aupairparisi#internlifei#internabroadl#lifeabroadl#liveabroads#serialexpatpersonalgrowthjourney

desc: “would you be able to share what living in so many different places in your 20’s taught you?”  a question that came in my comments a couple of weeks ago as i was turning 33 and one that i wanted to answer in full...  my 20’s were adventurous, unforgettable and my greatest teacher. i learned that possibilities and opportunities depend more on your mindset and how you view them rather than logistics or ‘limitations.’ if you believe anything is possible, it will be...  i learned that you need not worry about losing closeness with your friends and family .. when you already have strong foundations, they will not only stay no matter how far or for how long you travel, but support, accept and love that part of you too. i learned that everyone has a story, to not be judgemental, to remain open, to embrace opportunities that may spontaneously arrive and let go of plans that may instead fall through ..  i learned that when you expand, your own world and your views, you can no longer fit into conventional societal expectations, even if you try. freedom becomes part of your dna and anything less is hard to settle for.  as a result of that i learned that’s worth trying everything to create or keep a life you absolutely love, rather than staying on a path where you know you won’t be happy. and that you can change course and start over as many times as you want.  and most importantly i learned that following my heart is the only way to feel peace. above security, material things and what society deems as success, true wealth is determined by how much time you spend doing the things you love.  the list could go on. my 20’s taught me a lot and it’s laid the foundation of life in my 30’s knowing more than ever who i am, what i like and dislike, what my values are, what’s important to me and how i want to live.  but the most important teaching of all, is that the lessons and learning never end… and for that, I’m grateful. ✨  . . . . . #madetotravel #createyourdreamlife #intuitiveliving #slowtraveller #freedomlifestyle #freedomlife #lifejourney #slowtravel #slowtraveller #digitalnomadlifestyle #freespirit #womentravelsolo #solofemaletravel desc: if you find yourself in berlin during the chilly season, 📌 save these suggestions for some less touristy things to do: • vabali ~ a “textile free” spa - meaning no swimwear so if you don’t mind going nude, this is the city’s best spa 👙🚫  • walk through the beautiful tiergarten park and make your way to café am neuen see to warm up with a hot drink by their (four!) log fires  • markthalle neun ~ indoor street food festival on thursdays • take a walk through mon bijou park and on to tadshikes teestube ~ shoes off, sit on pillows on the floor and enjoy a whole menu of teas • rhinoçéros ~ evening small jazz bar playing vinyl only • enjoy an exhibition (current faves: monets garden, lighthouse of digital arts, dark matter)  • the planetarium  • shakespeare & son for books and bagels  • cafe pförtner - a hot drink (and food) on an old bus with the fire burning  . . . . . #thisisberlin #berlinlocal #berlinexpat #berlincafe #cafeberlin #hiddengems #secretspots #localfinds #berlincity #prenzlauerberg #freespirit #freedomlifestyle #createyourdreamlife #madeformore #slowtraveller #madetottravel #slowtravel #femalefounder #digitalnomadlifestyle #freespirit #fulltimetraveller #womentravelsolo #solofemaletravel #berlinliving #berlinwinter

desc: in my early 20’s i always had the belief that one day i would need to settle down, get a ‘real job’ and work my way up the corporate ladder as so many of us do. and this is the reason that whilst travelling, i always made sure that i did ‘something for my cv’ whether it be working at different companies, taking a language course in the country i was in, volunteering or doing extra studies along the way.  at 25 i entered my new office, to work in PR for an international agency in Berlin. and to be brief, it was three years and three promotions later, nearing burnout and feeling my soul slip away, that i got the message. “this life is not meant for you.”  and i knew it to be true. so at 28, with no financial reserve but a lot of drive to change direction, i quit my job and founded my own business (@homemade_studio 😘), then one more during lockdown (@nawaste.co) whilst also freelancing on the side.  it took a fair few years of hard work and fair few more sacrifices, but i made it back to having the freedom to experience living/working from different places around the world … and this time, purely on my terms and without an expiry date. 🦋 people ask if the decision to was scary. and i can honestly say that it wasn’t … it was the thought of staying where I was and where that path was heading that terrified me much much more ✨ i share this because your soul knows. if you feel called to have a lifestyle like this, not rooted in the traditional 9-5 path, it’s because you’re meant to. and you can 🤍 . . . . . #cre#createyourdreamlifeo#slowtravellerd#madetottravele#freedomlifestylee#freedomlifef#lifejourneyt#authenticexperiencec#localfindsd#hiddengemsc#secretspotso#slowtravelu#founderstoryg#digitalnomadlifestyleg#digitalnomadlifere#freespiritl#fulltimetravellerm#womentravelsolol#solofemaletravelad#madeformorei#spiritualgrowthjourneyl#selftrustrsonalgrowthjourney

desc: L’utilizzo delle sbarre può essere un ottimo modo per migliorare anche il tuo  livello di boxe! Richiedono una forte presa e un notevole sforzo della parte superiore del corpo, in particolare delle braccia, delle spalle e del dorso.  Questo tipo di allenamento può contribuire a sviluppare una maggiore forza nelle tue braccia e nei tuoi muscoli del torace, importanti per lanciare colpi potenti e per sostenere il tuo corpo durante i movimenti di difesa. Per eseguire correttamente gli esercizi alle sbarre, è necessario impegnare il core per mantenere l’equilibrio e la stabilità durante i movimenti. Questo aiuterà a rafforzare i muscoli addominali e della schiena, fornendo una base solida per i tuoi movimenti quando ti muovi in guardia da boxe. Per allenare le gambe, concentrati sugli Squat jump che essendo un esercizio Pliometrico, contribuirà a sviluppare una maggiore potenza nelle gambe, che potrai sfruttare durante le combinazioni di colpi e i movimenti esplosivi sul ring. L’attrezzatura che ti serve è semplice e la puoi trovare: in palestra, al parchetto o anche a casa (con un piccolo investimento)! No scuse! Se ti è piaciuto questo contenuto metti like e condividilo con chi pensi  possa servirgli!  💥💥💥 . . . . . #boxe #calisthenics #allenamentocorpolibero #addominali #trazioni #trazioniallasbarra #pullups #pushup #pugilato #pugilatoitaliano #ptdubai #dubaimarina #personaltraineritalia #motivazionale #tonificazione #digitalnomad #digitalnomadlife #digitalnomadlifestyle #remotework #workfromanywhere #дубай #милан #италия #locationindependent #freelance #backpacker #traveltheworld

desc: On my last video I got a lot of people trying to say that what I offer is a “scam” and let me inform you how ridiculous that is. If I didn’t sign up for a virtual assistant coaching program and work with my coach hands on I would STILL be in the same place I was before. Depressed. Miserable. Stuck in a job and life that was unfulfilling.  I think it’s good to be skeptical, but to call other people out for literally HELPING others like someone helped me is absolute BS!!! This is real, I actually give a FUCK about helping women start their own businesses if they want something more out of life. If you don’t believe, you don’t have to, but the rest of us that actually give a fuck about bettering ourselves and taking action towards moving forward are always going to come out strong in the end. The only way you can achieve what you want in this life is to go out and get it PERIOD. If you want to learn how, comment “how” on this post if your serious about learning and I’ll send you more info. desc: Respuesta a @nixonsonkiondo Follow me on Instagram for more travel content! ✈️🌍 Ig: @lauraabornstein This is a quick overview of how to start traveling the world full-time.   There's soooo much more I could say about this, so if you have any questions feel free to leave them in the comments and I'll do my best to answer! I'd also like to mention that I myself haven't travelled full-time yet, although I'm well on my way and I am following the three steps I talk about in the video. I have also witnessed other people follow these steps and succesfully become digital nomads. This is because of various personal reasons, as well as having chosen an expensive region of the world to travel to (East Africa) 😅 which means it will take me longer to save up for full-time travel. #fulltimetravel #fulltimetraveler #fulltimetravelers #fulltimetravellers #howtotravel #howtotraveltheworld #howtotravelfulltime #digitalnomad #digitalnomadlife #digitalnomadlifestyle #digitalnomadtips #digitalnomadtravel

desc: that last weekend of October Berlin spirit.  my favourite kind of people? the free-spirits who have the courage to be no one but themselves. they don’t live bounded by expectations (societal or other), they understand that growing older doesn’t mean to stop playing, they dress how they wish, do what lights them up and they give others the feeling that they might just be able to live this way too, sooner rather than later.  and it’s one of the things i’ve always loved about Berlin. skate in your 30’s, ride a bike backwards whilst juggling, wear pink hair and a crop top as a man, take your pet cat or parrot to the park and no one will bat an eyelid… absolutely nothing is off limits here, in the name of living freely.  📍tempelhofer feld ~ an abandoned airport that’s turned into one of the best places for Berliners to picnic, skate, fly kites, play music, have  bbqs + + + . . . . . #t#thisisberlinb#berlincityb#berlinlifet#tempelhoferfelda#abandonedplacesa#abandonedplacef#freespiritf#freedomlifestylec#createyourdreamlifem#madeformores#slowtravellerm#madetottravels#slowtravelf#femalefounderd#digitalnomadlifestylee#exploregermanyf#freespiritf#fulltimetravellerw#womentravelsolos#solofemaletravelb#berlinlivingb#berlinautumnexploreberlin

stickersText:
['Tau nggak sih kalau WFH itu sebenernya nggak sama dengan Remote Working?', 'Memang sih similar,
sama2 bekerja secara online.', 'Bedanya remote work nggak terikat peraturan atau punya peraturan perusahaan yg bebas terkait tempat & waktu bekerja. Mau kerja di pantai, gunung, negara/kota lain, beach club, cafe, timezone yg beda juga aman.. asal ada internet.', 'Sementara, walau sama2 online, WFH somehow tetap tunduk dg peraturan2 tertentu terkait waktu & tempatnya and biasanya di set untuk kasih suasana baru ke pekerjanya. Cuma, kasarannya tidak sebebas remote working.', 'Dan dengan kebebasan yg dimiliki sama orang2 yg kerja remote work muncul juga life style digital nomad. Lifestyle dimana orang traveling atau hidup berpindah2 di banyak kota/negara yg berbeda sambil kerja secara online.

Definisi full time worker full time traveler 😂😅', 'Tapi apakah semua remote worker sudah pasti punya digital nomad lifestyle?
Belum tentu, ada juga yang memilih tinggal disitu2 aja dan nggak traveling kesana kemari, but bekerja secara remote (and that’s okay too).', 'Kalau kamu lebih suka WFH atau Remote Working (digital nomad) nih? 😁😄'], ['WFH vs Remote Working
+ digital nomad lifestyle']

desc: Let me say it louder for the people in the back… There is no one way to make an income remotely! It’s SO IMPORTANT to do work that is aligned with your personality, skillset, and interests so that you dont get burned out and end up moving back to moms house with your tail between your legs.  Want to become a digital nomad but dont know what remote job YOU can do? I have a bunch of free resources linked in my bio: a live coaching session, a 3-hour training (“how to get started as a digital nomad) and my podcast (the digital nomad life podcast). desc: Knock knock! Opportunity is calling! Don’t be silly like me and wait! The longer you wait, the more time spent doing what you love and money earned is passing you by! are you somebody that wants to work from anywhere and travel the world? Virtual assistant Work can do that for you! I’ve been able to travel to multiple places while working from my laptop or phone!  this job has given me the ultimate freedom to live on my own terms because I am my own boss! I personally know how frustrating it can be to feel stuck in a job that doesn’t fuel your fire! that’s why it’s important to always put yourself first because we only get one life and you should live it how you deserve! virtual assistant work is the best because you can start with no experience and no degree and get your foot in the door into this crazy online space! Working online is truly unmatched and I would want this life for anybody!  virtual assistants take on tasks that business owners don’t have time to do or don’t like to do! you don’t have to have all the skills in the world, just be coachable and ready to learn! If you want to learn how to comment on my video with the word “HOW” and I will reach out to you with more information! #virtuala#virtualassistantjourneya#virtualassistantlifea#virtualassistantsalaryh#10kmonthsm#workfromanywherelifen#digitalnomadlifestylec#echocoaching
hashtagNames: virtualassistantjourney, virtualassistantlife, virtualassistantsalary, 10kmonths, workfromanywherelife, digitalnomadlifestyle, echocoaching

desc: Counting down the days🥹 • • Off to Colombia for a month of endless possibilities 🌎✨ I’m thrilled to be stepping into a co-living space for the entire month of November with other remote workers, students, and CREATIVES!! This is seriously the inspiration I’ve needed since falling back into quite the funk in my hometown lol I’m so so excited to meet the beautiful souls & connect on a deeper level, sharing stories, insights, & dreams. The chance to learn from each other & grow collectively, all while immersing ourselves in the rich culture of Colombia is an adventure I’m embracing with open arms 🇨🇴 And who knows? The journey might not end there! Leaving it open ended for now to give me the chance to dive headfirst, straight into the next adventure ;)  Be sure to stick around for all the travel prep, packing tips, & Colombia content in the coming months 🤍 #solofemaletravel #colombiatravel #visitcolombia #travelcreator #fulltimetraveler #digitalnomadlifestyle #howtotravel #travellifestyle #internationaltravel

stickersText:
['Wanna have a real conversation?

Yes, having a completely remote job with a digital nomad lifestyle is one of my best decision. Yes, most of the time it feels like I’m living my best life.

YET it can feel shitty too sometimes. You can feel overworked, you’re stressed with the new environment, home sick, it won’t always be the travelling vibe all the time, and you gotta be used to farewells & letting go.

But it’s ok. We choose our own challenge and the ups & downs are only the part of our stories :)'], ['Another Side of
The Story']

desc: Replying to @generic_user_name_  Finding a remote job that allows you to travel both nationally internationally can be a really tough time especially if you're trying to live the digital nomad or full time traveler lifestyle like I am. There are career search tools online that I was able to find such as trulyremote.co and there are companies that do seemingly hire international remote workers such as Spotify, Zapier and Atlassian.  The other best option is  To choose a career that allows you to travel remote regardless or makes it more likely such as copywriting, freelance work, e-commerce, software development,  Is teaching English online, etc.  My last piece of advice would be to travel to a place and work there like with a Woking Holiday Vusa or to work a contract job in the United States to save up enough money to travel internationally.  Let me know if you have any more questions on working remotely internationally and I hope this helps! #digitalnomad #digitalnomadlifestyle #fulltimetravel #fulltimetraveler #fulltimetravelers #remotejobs #digitalnomadlife #digitalnomadjobs #remotejobsearch

desc: Passive income is real thing Yall!!! I’m not saying it didn’t take hard work up front- because it did. It was NOT PASSIVE at all in the beginning and It was grueling with little to no money in at first. But my VISION and my hard work paid off and now my Etsy print on demand shop makes me passive income while I LIVE my life with my family. I am so grateful that I saw the vision and took action. I want you to know that you can have this life too!!  #teacherquittok #teachersoftiktok #printondemand #etsysellersoftiktok #sidehustler #printondemandshop #digitalnomadlifestyle #smallbusinesstiktok #printondemandbusiness #makemoneyinyoursleep #passiveincome #passiveincomelifestyles
hashtagNames: teacherquittok, teachersoftiktok, printondemand, etsysellersoftiktok, sidehustler, printondemandshop, digitalnomadlifestyle, smallbusinesstiktok, printondemandbusiness, makemoneyinyoursleep, passiveincome, passiveincomelifestyles
stickersText: ['Just traveled from US back to Greece. Over 24 hours- didn’t lay a finger on my Etsy shop and still made TRIPLE than what I use to make in a day as a teacher. \nI won’t be touching my shop for another day or so. My orders are synced to the printing company so I don’t have to do anything AND It will continue to make me passive income while we explore/ recover from jet lag. '], ['Passive income is a real thing ']

desc: i travelled so much in my 20’s, moving to 6 different countries back to back across 6 years, because i thought it may be my only chance… “experience living everywhere you want to, before you have to settle down” is what i told myself.  but what i didn’t know then, that i’ve come to learn after a few more years of life lessons, is that it is possible to create a lifestyle that has both. where you can work for yourself online and travel for as long and far as you want to.  this is the lifestyle that seems to have chosen me, and that i fully chosen back - and one that i don’t think i will ever need to retire from. 🥰 i share this in the hopes that it reaches those who may be asking questions in this area right now … and to say that if you too feel called to have a lifestyle like this, not rooted in the traditional 9-5 path, it’s because you’re meant to. and you can 🤍 . . . . . #madetotravel #createyourdreamlife #intuitiveliving #slowtraveller #freedomlifestyle #freedomlife #lifejourney #slowtravel #slowtraveller #digitalnomadlifestyle #freespirit #womentravelsolo #solofemaletravel #traveldiary  #london #newyork #brazil #paris #copenhagen #berlin #bali #provence

desc: People always tell me how they want to travel like me or have my life, and I have two things to say to that: 1. My life isn't all that you see on social media. There's a lot (both good and bad) that I don't post here. I have my issues, just like anyone else. But perhaps most importantly, I don't travel as much as it looks like on social media. Don't get me wrong, I travel a lot, but as an aspiring content creator I have to post travel content on a daily basis, several times a day, across multiple platforms. I can assure you I don't travel every day, or every week or every month. 2. Everyone comes from a different background and I've been very lucky when it comes to travel. I'm not going to sit here and deny my priviledge.  That said, no one handed this life to me. The content creation, solo travel and potentially being a full-time traveler, that was all me. It all started with a decision to change the way I lived and take risks in order to pursue what I wanted. And more importantly, action followed that decision. That is the most important thing. #travellife #travellifestyle #travellife✈️ #digitalnomad #digitalnomadlife #digitalnomadlifestyle #digitalnomadtravel

desc: The digital nomad Visa is the perfect  Way to see and live in another country if you have a job that is remote or if you work for yourself. These countries will let you live there as long as you can prove that you make a certain income which most of the time is their minimum wage. Here are all the countries that I mentioned,  Norway Bahamas Portugal Germany  Barbados Greece Iceland Romania  Indonesia Italy Spain Taiwan and Mexico.  I also mentioned Australia New Zealand Ireland South Korea and Singapore do not have this program but will let you stay there for a year with a  working holiday Visa which I can talk about in another video.  As a full time traveler and digital nomad and backpacker these are some of the best tools to use to see the world for cheap, it is also a great alternative to the gap year. Which country would you go to? #digitalnomadlifestyle #digitalnomad #digitalnomadvisa #fulltiemtravel #fulltimetraveler #gapyear #travellife

desc: June 20th: I’m hosting a FREE coaching call for anyone who wants to learn how to become a Digital Nomad!  Make sure you RSVP for it because I host on zoom and there wre limited spots. If you are ready to create a dream career, dream income, dream LIFE for yourself,  this event is for you. desc: follow your intuition. the more along the journey i go, the more i understand that how badly we feel or how much we suffer, is just an indication of how much further we are moving away from the life that is meant for us. by nature, that is the design of our emotional guidance system.  and so when something in your life really needs to change, you will know. you’ll sense it, because we will have an inner guide that speaks to us through feelings, and those ‘it just doesn’t feel right’ emotions will get stronger and stronger until the very moment you take that very first step in another direction that make you feel little flutters of excitement and hope instead. 🤍 do you pay attention to those little signs from your intuition/inner guide? . . . . . #createyourdreamlife #slowtraveller #madetottravel #freedomlifestyle #freedomlife #lifejourney #authenticexperience #localfinds #hiddengems #secretspots #slowtravel #founderstory #digitalnomadlifestyle #digitalnomadlife  #freespirit #fulltimetraveller #womentravelsolo #solofemaletravel  #madeformore #spiritualgrowthjourney #selftrust #personalgrowthjourney

desc: 📍Maligne Canyon, Jasper National Park  The deepest canyon in Jasper National Park. Measuring a depth of over 50 metres at certain points, hikers of all abilities are able to explore this amazing, all natural landscape by crossing 6 bridges which are built at various different points throughout the canyon.  With the 2nd bridge standing at the highest point of the canyon, the 3rd bridge is by far the best view you’ll get of the stunning waterfall which allows for some incredible photo opportunities. #travelbucketlist #affordabletravel #travelcouple #waterfalls #jaspernationalpark #explorealberta #travelcanada #travelblogger #digitalnomadlife #digitalnomadlifestyle #hiketok #hikealberta #hikingtips

desc: Someone I'm close with recently told me I had to think about how I was going to spend the rest of my life. It was a long and ugly conversation. I've been speaking to this person for years about my desire to live life on my own terms, and not stick to a job for 40 years. This person also has no idea what I'm actually doing with my life right now or ehat I'm planning. They're so judgemental I don't tell them. I honestly found it so repulsive that even after knowing me for years, they didn't give a damn and just imposed their idea of life on me. I no longer speak to this person. Can anyone relate? #travellife #travellifestyle #digitalnomadlifestyle #digitalnomad #digitalnomadproblems #travelmindset

desc: Replying to @lisaserota  Here are all my budget travel tips and travel recommendations for someone going to visit Tokyo, Japan.  1st I would recommend  Going to all the different cities within Tokyo, Japan such as shinjuku shibuya asakusa rapungi and so on.  Then I would also recommend going to Tokyo Disneyland and sea, the studio ghibli museum, the Ramen museum, TeamLABS Tokyo and some of the more popular places like Sensoji temple, Tokyo sky tree, Tsukiji fish market, and the Imperial palace.  As for food I would recommend trying yakaniku and ramen as well as my favorite Japanese chicken Katsu curry, CoCo Ichibanya is great quick and easy for katsu curry but I may also recommend somewhere that isn't a chain that specializes in katsu curry. Additionally, I would also recommend going outside of the city to Fuji, Kyoto, Osaka and Himeji with the JR Rail pass. #tokyotravel #visittokyo #budgettraveller #budgettraveltips #fulltimetravel #fulltimetraveller #digitalnomads #japantraveltips #visitjapan #digitalnomadlifestyle
hashtagNames: , tokyotravel, visittokyo, budgettraveller, budgettraveltips, fulltimetravel, fulltimetraveller, digitalnomads, japantraveltips, visitjapan, digitalnomadlifestyle

desc: How to find remote work 👇 (SAVE for your job hunt!) I’ve had THE BEST summer in Europe! I spent time in Malta, Ibiza & then spent 7 nights Sailing around Croatia! My heart feels so full from all the amazing people I met, the cold Aperol I drank & the opportunities I got through social media which I never would’ve dreamt were possible this time last year (thank you ALL OF YOU for following and being part of this community, you’re changing my life & I hope I am helping you to change your’s & live this life too!) In a couple of weeks, I’m heading to Bali, Thailand then Sri Lanka & Nepal to host group trips! If you guys want to join me then send me a DM for info! If you want to live this full-time travel, digital nomad life then I’m here to help & cheer you on every step of the way bebeh! No matter what age 🎉 It took a LONG TIME to figure this out and made many mistakes along the way but now I’m sharing it all with you! First up: you could get a remote job! To find one, try these websites: * angel.co * remote.co * remotewomen.com * inkedin.com/jobs * workingnomads.com * nodesk.co * weworkremotely.com * FlexJobs * Fiverr * Upwork  If you want to travel long term but don’t fancy a laptop job then you could try:  1/ Working holiday visas: allow you to live & work in certain countries such as Australia & NZ for up to 2 years.  2/ Seasonal Work: Companies hire people in various roles to go & work a winter or summer season at their resort/ hotel/ camp. Usually, you get flights, accommodation, food & pay! 3/ Work for Accommodation: volunteer at a place in exchange for free accom. OR, you can collaborate & create content for places, again in exchange for free accom (you can charge for this sometimes too) 4/ Trip leader: Tour companies hire you to lead the trip. So you go on trips around whichever country/ city etc.  I go over all these details in my ebook: 6 Ways to Work & Travel the World, which is currently 50% off, only $15 :) Follow @daisystraveldiaries for daily tips on how to travel solo as a digital nomad 🥰 . . . #travel #digitalnomad #digitalnomads #digitalnomadlifestyle #fulltimetravel #travelfulltime #workandtravel #remotework #remoteworking
hashtagNames: travel, digitalnomad, digitalnomads, digitalnomadlifestyle, fulltimetravel, travelfulltime, workandtravel, remotework, remoteworking

desc: Hi, I’m Nic and I’ve been a self employed digital nomad for nearly 5 years 🤓.  I chose this lifestyle so I could travel the world and live life on my own terms 🫶🏼 Before becoming a digital nomad I had experience in Retail Store Management, HR and being an Executive Assistant. Unfortunately, my job at the time wouldn’t allow for remote working so I quit and started gigging across multiple jobs, CV Writing, Personal Assistance and Copy Typing. However, I knew I wanted to become a Content Creator as I wanted to do something more creative with my life that complimented my love for travelling so… I started documenting my life here on Instagram 🤟🏼.  After a few years, I decided to start a YouTube followed by a TikTok and next thing I know I was able to make Content Creation my full time job 🥰.  I’m a big believer in not having all your eggs in one basket when it comes to generating financial streams so I also offer coaching sessions focused on Content Creation and Van Life as well as creating and selling eBooks. When I have spare time, I make jewellery and tattoo as well 🙃 If you have any questions about being a digital nomad, ask away in the comments below 🥰 @NicRoams @NicRoams  . . #v#vanlifed#digitalnomads#selfemployeds#selfemployedlifes#selfemploymentd#digitalnomadlifed#digitalnomadsw#workforyourselfv#vanlifert#travellerf#fulltimevanliferf#fulltimetravellert#traveleverydayd#digitalnomadlifestyled#digitalnomadgirlsd#digitalnomaden#nomadlifen#nomadictnomadstories

desc: I don’t support communism, in fact I hate it because that’s the reason why my grandmother had to escape Hungary back in 1956 with my mother in her arms through hills and wire.  However, the remains of Buzludzha are impressive not only for the shape and size but for the psychological effect it has on you as you’re approaching it and you get close to it. From the distance it looks like a spaceship that’s ready to take off and you can barely notice the bad state it is which can be only seeing once you’re next to it when you get to the top.  I will never say this is beautiful but I will say that it is on its own a good example of human legacy that hopefully never comes back again.  #bulgaria #solotraveller #digitalnomad #digitalnomadlife #digitalnomadlifestyle #easterneuropetrip

desc: I swam aboard a sexy man’s boat this day, for real 👀👇 (Save & share with someone who’d do this) What really happened in this video: a group of friends and I went out on a boat in Ibiza where we drank rose, danced, swam & lived our best lives. As you can see I just love to dance & groove so was in the zone then my friends drone scared the EFF out of me. But carried on anyway… I also love my friends in the background joining in the groove 🤣 On this day I also hijacked a neighbouring boat 😂. I saw a sailing boat close to ours with some beautiful men on board & it looked like they lived in it so I wanted to know their story… I jumped into the water with my bucket hat on, swam over and started chatting to them. They gave me a beer and let me have a look on the boat (it was close to our boat though & i made sure I was in sight of my friends at all times as safety first). I then jumped off the bow & swam back to my friends… it felt like a true mamma mia moment 😆 Turns out the owner is an Italian guy who lets people live on his boat all summer to help him out sailing around the Med. Then in the winter he worked for theatre companies!  Sooo cool. This is my fav part of traveling, hearing other people’s stories in the world 🌸 What’s your fav travel story you’ve learnt from a stranger? 🎉 Follow @daisystraveldiaries for daily travel & digital nomad tips 🌸 . . . #digitalnomadlifestyle #digitalnomadgirl #travel #solotravel #remoteworking #ibiza
hashtagNames: digitalnomadlifestyle, digitalnomadgirl, travel, solotravel, remoteworking, ibiza
stickersText: ['When the dating apps aren’t working so you hop on a boat in Ibiza & dance to attract a sexy man with a yacht & then… ', 'Then you actually end up on a sexy man’s boat 👀👇']

desc: after the second week of living somewhere new, something changes and you no longer quite feel like a tourist on holiday. you’ve experienced enough things to know … which boulangeries make your favourite pain au chocolates (you know the ones with the crunchy flakes that have been baked to perfection😍), you know at which time your favourite cafes will be drenched in sun (just before it gets too busy) and can greet the waiter by name… you know what time you need to put the bin out on the street in order to be collected, what days the fresh markets are and plan your shopping  accordingly and you can navigate the maze of alleyways without relying on your google maps…  and that’s where the true appreciation comes in. for experiencing life of another set of people, in another coordinate of the world... this moment in time of a certain place, walking in the shoes of another and trying out an alternate life to see how it fits. 🇫🇷 and you … how long does it usually take you to feel ‘settled in’ in a new place?  📍aix en provence . . . . . #madeformore #createyourdreamlife #madetottravel #freedomlifestyle #freedomlife #digitalnomadlifestyle #slowtravel #slowtraveller #slowtravelling #lifejourney #authenticexperience #localfinds #localtips #freespirit #fulltimetraveller #womentravelsolo #solofemaletravel #solofemaletraveler #solofemaletraveller #provence #provencelife #aixenprovence

desc: re-meeting Paris as different versions of myself 🥰🤍 the importance of the notion ‘enjoy the now’ that we hear so often took on a whole deeper meaning for me during my time in Paris.  walking the streets and remembering my ‘9 years ago’ version of me who had done the same. finding myself sat here in the very spot that was once an abandoned hospital and my secret place to enter at night with the notre dame in full view, a friend and a bottle of wine in hand. i mean, i remember clearly feeling that it was a special experience then … but i hadn’t considered how much and how those moments would never be replicated.  because at some point over the last 9 years, the hospital reopened and it’s no longer the place with deserted hallways i once knew. now it’s only accessible if you are a visiting a patient … or you manage to charm the security guard with nostalgic stories until they surprisingly reach under the desk for a visitors pass, hand it to you with a secret smile and nod and permit you entry 😅.  so on this day, by chance and with luck, i sat in this same spot for perhaps the last time in my life 🥹. taking it all in.  and i thought about how moments become memories so quickly and how often, we may not fully appreciate and see them as the unique moment in time that they are.   and this is the re-reminder i was given. to fully enjoy, be present and conscious on every single trip taken and every single experience ... because yes, you may have the chance to be in the same places again, physically … but the experience of you, in this moment, at this age, as the you that you are right now … that will only ever happen once. . . . . . #madetot#madetotravely#createyourdreamlifei#intuitivelivinga#slowtravellerm#freedomlifestylem#freedomlifeu#lifejourneya#slowtravela#slowtravellerl#digitalnomadlifestylei#freespiritr#womentravelsolom#solofemaletravelp#rooftopview##parisa#notredames#travelstoriesi#expatlifeifestyle

desc: Can you believe that all these beautiful beach clubs are located almost next to each other in one of the most beautiful beaches of the world?  Here’s the list for your next visit on Isla Mujeres:  1.- Lima y Coco 2.- Las Hamacas  3.- Green Demon  4.- Gurú 5.- Tarzan’s Bar If you want to relax and prefer empty beaches like in this video we suggest you get there early. As the day goes by they start to get a bit crowded so if you’re looking for fun and a live environment stay until sunset time.  Save this post for your next visit and follow us for more Isla Mujeres tips.  ¿Puedes creer que todos estos hermosos clubes de playa están ubicados muy cerca uno del otro en una de las playas más hermosas del mundo?  Aquí está la lista para tu próxima visita a Isla Mujeres:  1.- Tarzán Bar  2.- Las Hamacas  3.- Green Demon  4.- Guru  5.- Lima y Coco  Si quieres relajarte y prefieres playas vacías como en este video te sugerimos que llegues temprano.  A medida que pasa el día, comienzan a llenarse un poco, así que si buscas diversión y un ambiente más vivo, quédate hasta la puesta del sol. desc: 🤯 I quit my office job 5 years ago and this is what my life looks like now 🤯 Yes, I still work, I just don’t live to work, I work to live 🙌🏼. Meaning my work, works around the life I want. A life where I feel as free as I can and in control of how I spend it 🫶🏼 When I was working my office job, I never understood how people made the leap, I’m going to admit it 😬… I thought wealth played a huge factor in it. But 5 years down the line I can promise you it doesn’t. When I started this life I was in debt, I had -£3000 in my bank. I was living in London, renting a flat in zone 2 and felt like I was grafting with no reward. The world I was living in was eating away my money, my freedom and my soul.  So I made huge changes, ones that I had no idea would work at the time and ones that scared the hell out of me.  But I can tell you right now, I’m so f**king grateful for past me… feeling very Snoop Dogg right now when he thanks himself for his hard work 😂. But we should all be proud of the choices we have made especially when it works out! The changes weren’t an overnight thing but this is how I basically did it 🧚‍♀️  1. I got a remote job in my evenings whilst working full time 2. I bought a van to become my home 3. When the van was done I quit my office job and left renting, the income from my remote job was enough to keep the wheels rolling and pay off the debt I had accumulated  4. With my spare hours, I enjoyed life and started the business I wanted to do, become a Content Creator There were a lot of hurdles along the way, it really isn’t as simple as a list but if you want it, keep your mind focused and take every challenge as a lesson 🫶🏼 I love helping you guys tread your own path so if you have any questions ask away in the comments below 👇🏽 @NicRoams @NicRoams  #dig#digitalnomadlifem#nomadlivingg#digitalcreatorst#alternativelifestylev#livingontheroadv#livinginavanl#fulltimetravellerm#nomadictn#vanlifera#travellerlifeg#digitalnomadlifestylem#nomadgirlsngirlsrule

desc: Today’s #travelvlog was an interesting one! Our bike route was a bit more difficult with the unfinished road, which was muddy and filled with water from the storm. We were prepared to have our feet soaked in mud, but thankfully there were enough rocks for us to stand on to push our bikes through!  The mud dried on our bike supee fast though, making it difficult to clip in. We stopped at a little store to have ice cream and some food, and to use the rest of our euros! Then we crossed the border into Serbia!  Another wild storm tonight, and this time the wifi went out as did the water. We still had cell service, so we continued to work with data. Seeing the aftermath of the storm was shocking, especially seeing the lamposts that were snapped in half! Super grateful that we were inside the whole time!  #digitalnomad #digitalnomadlifestyle #biketouring #biketour #serbia #storm

desc: slow travel isn't always necessarily to do with time. it's true that we don't always have the opportunity to spend a few weeks or months in one place, but even still, we can slow down our pace.  avoid trying to squeeze everywhere and everything in, making a checklist of must do's and a plan to see them back to back, let go of spending time in the popular places that actually don't make your soul light up and release any feelings of guilt that may come with believing that you're seeing less. by doing this, you'll come away with actually experiencing more. go on long walks without a set direction, stopping at whichever place, restaurant or cafe that 'just feels good,' to you, be open to long conversations with strangers, and spend some leisurely time watching the world go by and soaking it all in. by all means, have a little pre-list of highlights you'd love to see, but stay open to the flow and the beauty that comes with going slow. 📍aix en provence . . . . . #madeformore #createyourdreamlife #madetottravel #freedomlifestyle #freedomlife #digitalnomadlifestyle #slowtravel #slowtraveller #slowtravelling #lifejourney #authenticexperience #localfinds #localtips #freespirit #fulltimetraveller #womentravelsolo #solofemaletravel #solofemaletraveler #solofemaletraveller #provence #provencelife #aixenprovence

desc: Part 2 of my nomad story! #digitalnomadlifestyle #digitalnomad #nomadlife #digitalnomadgirl #workremotelyjobs #workandtravel
hashtagNames: digitalnomadlifestyle, digitalnomad, nomadlife, digitalnomadgirl, workremotelyjobs, workandtravel
stickersText:
['How I traveled the 🌍 as Digital Nomad PART 2', 'I got my first remote job offer while I was on a 2-week trip to Costa Rica.

 I was sitting by the pool on the phone with my new boss and he said, “as long as you have good wifi and are online when you need to be online, I don’t care where you are.” ', 'I called Spirit Airline to see if I could change my flight to a later date & MIRACULOUSLY I got a full refund! Suddenly I was in Central America with a full-time remote job, no return flight… & a party I wanted to attend in Nicaragua!', 'The party was AMAZING. I couldn’t believe I didn’t have to go home after it!

I promised myself there was no way I’d F* this up & I’d do anything to be the MOST RELIABLE employee ever. After a month of traveling, my boss was happy & started giving me better projects.', 'I moved on from Nica to Colombia. Then to Ecuador, Brazil… at first I was only SOLO TRAVELING but eventually I started  meeting other people who called themselves “Digital Nomads,” (I never heard the term before!)', 'The more nomad friends I made, the more I felt like my travel lifestyle was sustainable… & it WAS.

I ended up living out of my suitcase for 5 years straight! I traveled to 60 countries while making good money & so many amazing friends.', 'After years at my job I quit in the middle of the pandemic to help people become digital nomads too. Now I’m a coach!

I use my intuitive gifts to determine which remote business they should create & then guide them through creating their biz and setting up their own traveling lifestyle.']

desc: What Sou does in🥁... Seoul! Episode 13 Looking for a unique and interactive activity in Seoul? Join me for a fun and unique experience in Seoul: Making traditional rice cakes! 🌸 I had an absolute blast making traditional rice cakes, and you can too! 🍡✨ 🕰️ Duration: Approximately 1 hour 💰 Price: 65.000₩ per person ⏰ Availability: Almost every day at 4:00 pm and sometimes at 7:00 pm These delicious and pretty rice cakes are made off bean paste, rice flour, and wheat flour. And don't be fooled, the shapes were not easy to make! Especially if you have long nails 🤣 But don't worry, the talented Chef Jinsil will guide you through the process, and help you shaping them beautifully. 🎨👩‍🍳 You can book this experience through: 1️⃣ Airbnb experiences 2️⃣ Klook 3️⃣ Or simply by sliding into @sunnysdiningofficial dms on Instagram Jinsil is an amazing chef who's always happy to lend a helping hand and answer any questions you may have. 🌟 📍 Seoul, Mapo-ku, Baek bum-ro 199, Metro the o'ville, 18th floor. 🚇 Take exit 6 at Gongdeok station, and you'll find the building right in front of you. Don't miss out on this delightful activity and create fun memories in Seoul. 🥰🌸  . . . . . #travelblogger #travelblog #travelvlogger #travelvlog #traveladdict #traveladventures #contentcreator #digitalnomad #adventure #funtravels #travelplanner #traveldiary #dailyadventures #digitalnomadlifestyle #travelcontentcreator #travel #traveltips #solofemaletravel #solofemaletraveler #seoul #ricecake #whatsoudoes #korea #koreatravel #seoulkorea

desc: “you have your head in the clouds.” i remember this sentence so well. it came from an ex partner, after me attempting to express how working a 9-5 was impacting me, how i felt that this surely couldn’t be it … surely my best years of freedom weren’t behind me … surely, there had to be more 🥺.  “you have your head in the clouds, this is the real world.” his statement, his belief, his misunderstanding. your dreams are yours. protect them, love them, follow them.  will you share here, what your dreams are? sometimes writing them down can be the action that sets them into motion 🤍 📍 cafe am neuen see (in my opinion Berlin’s best beer garden, especially on a warm sunny day)  . . . . . #cre#createyourdreamlifeo#slowtravellerd#madetottravele#freedomlifestylee#freedomlifef#lifejourneyt#authenticexperiencec#localfindsd#hiddengemsc#secretspotso#slowtravelu#founderstoryg#digitalnomadlifestyleg#digitalnomadlifere#freespiritl#fulltimetravellerm#womentravelsolol#solofemaletravelad#madeformorei#spiritualgrowthjourneyl#selftrustrsonalgrowthjourney

desc: Bismillah  Capek, tapi ini adalah hal yang dulu aku cita-cita kan. Bisa kerja dari mana aja, dimana saja, sekalipun pake piyama.  Dulu aku gak kepikiran sama sekali buat jadi Freelancer, tapi alhamdulillah ternyata ini justru menjadi awal yang baik. Jadi Freelancer beneran bisa menambah pemasukan yang luar biasa banget ngaruhnya untuk membantu kantong mahasiswa yang kuliah di Jababeka ini. Alhamdulillah selama kuliah gak minta uang saku ke orang tua lagi, segala keperluan udah dipenuhi sendiri. Bersyukur banget.  Buat temen-temen yang pengen jadi Freelancer, ambil kesempatan itu mulai dari sekarang. Modalnya cuma kemauan buat belajar yaa, karena yang dibutuhin itu skill yang kita harus latih dan pelajari. Bismillah pasti ada jalan, karena setiap hari selalu ada kerjaannya. Dari dalam dan luar negeri semua ada. Bismillah pasti bisa.  #digitalnomadlifestyle #digitalnomad #fyp #freelance #digitalmarketing #freelancer #parttime #WFA #percayaproses #growthmindset #selfdevelopment
