desc: Nunca sabemos con exactitud que pasará mañana, vivas el sedentarismo o el nomadismo. Lo único que está seguro, es que como sedentarios viviremos algo parecido al día de hoy y como nómadas seguramente alguna nueva experiencia. Tu eliges cuanto repetir los días, semana, meses o años, nosotros elegimos ser Nómadas Digitales 🔝 porque deseamos conocer en qué planeta vivimos, cuántos modelos de pensamientos más hay entre tantos humanos, tradiciones, precios diferentes y probar comidas, ohh que placer 😋 ¡En la página web compartimos más!  🔗 www.NomadasDigitales.TOP (link en bio) 🗺️ No te avergüences de visitarnos, somos hospitalarios además te daremos una especial bienvenida. 🤩  © Ion Iacob @Editor, Chef y Marketing VIP  © Jacqueline M.Q. @Escritora & Asesora de Libros  #travellife #digitalnomadism #digitalnomading #laptoplifestyle #nomad #nomadasdigitalestop #travelblogger #digitalnomadlifestyle #freelance #digitalnomadsasia #digitalnomadlife #digitalnomadfamily #digitalnomadwomen #digitalnomad #travelblog #digitalnomade #digitalnomadspirit #digitalnomadkhan #nomadasdigitales #digitalnomadgirls #nomadastop #digitalnomaddiary #workfromanywhere #remotework #nomadlife #digitalnomadgirl #coworking

desc: Embracing New Beginnings in the Digital Nomad World! 🌍✨ Just like a sunset's promise of endless possibilities, starting a new career in the digital nomad world can be both exciting and daunting. Here are 2 essential tips to guide your journey: 1️⃣ Cultivate a Strong Online Presence: Build a professional website and utilize social media to showcase your skills and connect with like-minded individuals. Your online presence opens doors and creates opportunities. 2️⃣ Seek Remote Work Opportunities: Explore online job boards and freelancing platforms to find remote work aligned with your skills. Join digital nomad communities like Nomad Connects to discover collaborations and job leads. Take that leap of faith and unlock a world of digital nomad possibilities! 🌇💼 #DigitalNomadLife #NewCareerJourney #EmbraceFlexibility #DigitalNomadlifestyle #RemoteWorkOpportunities

desc: Here’s how I went from content creator > multi 6-figure online course creator 👇🏼 Comment “FREE COURSE” … and I’ll send you the link to my free course that shows you exactly how Story time: When I started pursuing content creation I realized… ✅ I was reaching thousands of people for free daily ✅ Brands were willing to pay me for the community I had built ✅ I had the potential to learn an unlimited income with low expenses with organic social media content ❌ Most people will choose to get paid a few hundred or even thousand dollars for a brand deal here and there (I’ve earned up to $9K per brand deal I took back in 2021) … but then I quickly realized I had spent my precious time building MY community so why not sell my own products and services? This is when I discovered online education: courses, coaching, mentoring, retreats, etc. I decided to take my personal transformation story (what I was already sharing on social media) and package it up into my own products and services Because of this… ✈️ I’m now leaving my 3 BED, 3 BATH NYC apartment to move to Bali and become a digital nomad with my boyfriend 🚀 Make up to $10,000 per day in my OWN online business, even when I take the day off (like I am here!) 📱 Help THOUSANDS of people worldwide through my content, courses, and mentorship — which is the most fulfilling path If you want to learn how… Comment “FREE COURSE” … and I’ll send you the link to my free course that shows you exactly how #contentcreator #onlinebusiness #onlinecoursecreators #digitalnomadlifestyle #contentcreatortips

desc: Have you heard of the "3 Foot Rule" in the home business space a. k. a network marketing business? Or this you are being brainwashed with : Everyone needs your products or business opportunities? Well, the short answer is : THIS IS NOT TRUE!!!! (that already goes against the principles of marketing) So stop wasting time and energy holding on to such beliefs given to you by "you-know-who". I was taught this during my old school, offline, 3 Foot Rule, business building days. It was relentless. And have no life. You don't have to make the same mistake as me. You can still be a marketer and yet a good human being at the same time.  Why we continue to allow the minority in the industry to teach the majority what don't work. desc: When I was younger I always thought that traveling the world would be a massive expense. Yes it can be, but it doesn’t have to be! Then 6 years ago, I learned how to travel hack! Beating The banks at their own game, leveraging travel reward bonuses to your benefit. The theory is to use a reward travel card on things or expenses you were already going to be purchasing. For me I used it to pay off my student loans, renovation and material cost for my properties, but it can be used for simple things like gas. However, the number one rule is NEVER let the card incure interest, and always have the money to pay off the card. after I learned this, haven’t been able to sit still since! ✈️🌎🗺📍#tra#travelhackl#balitravela#realestateinvestingg#augustay#diylandlordg#digitalnomadlifestyle
hashtagNames: travelhack, balitravel, realestateinvesting, augusta, diylandlord, digitalnomadlifestyle
stickersText: ['How buying more real estate got me a 2 week trip to Bali ', 'I purchased a distressed 4 unit property in Augusta Georgia ', 'I pulled a travel credit card with a sign on bonus ', 'I funneled all renovations and material cost through the card to meet the minimum spend ', 'Then renovated ', 'And renovated ', 'And renovated some more ', 'Once the renovations were complete, I increased rents ', 'And rented each unit at market rent ', 'Then got the points and booked the flight ✈️ ', 'For my flight nothing was spent out of pocket ', 'I did this same process with 2 other travel cards ', 'Then used the points to book this Air B N B', 'When done right, It’s called travel hacking', 'Beating the banks at their own game ']

desc: after one month of living in Aix en Provence, the charming walkable southern French city, i wanted to just leave a few bite-size recommendations which will take you straight to the ‘crème de la crème’ of things to enjoy if you plan to visit for a couple of days ☺️: • definitely take a slow stroll through the beautiful markets and all their organic local products, taking a bag of the famous herbs du provence home with you 🥰 (Tuesdays, Thursdays and Saturdays are the 3 big market days 🍓).  • if you’re a crepe lover 🙋🏽‍♀️ you’re going to want to find the underground pedestrian tunnel near the roundabout and Apple Store - in the small alleyway down there, you’ll see the little hole in the wall making the most authentic (and cheap) crepes  • enjoy more treats from ‘Bechard’ - voted the best bakery in the city by all the locals • cafes/bars/restos: ‘bacchus’ (this is a beautiful spot i went to oftennn because it was always in the sun/ and it’s on a square that felt more local. ‘les vieulles canailles’ for a very authentic French dining experience 🇫🇷 . . . . #madeformore #createyourdreamlife #madetottravel #freedomlifestyle #freedomlife #digitalnomadlifestyle #slowtravel #slowtraveller #slowtravelling #lifejourney #authenticexperience #localfinds #localtips #freespirit #fulltimetraveller #womentravelsolo #solofemaletravel #solofemaletraveler #solofemaletraveller #provence #provencelife #aixenprovence

desc: Email I send after an interview when I don’t get the job. It’s easy to take rejection personally But there are many reasons why you don’t get a job 1. Maybe the budget was cut and they lost the position 2. They could have promoted someone or demoted someone already at the company 3. Or Maybe they gave the job to someone else and that person quit after 1 week Either way, an email like this keeps your options open.  Email: Good afternoon, I want to thank you for your time on Monday. It was a pleasure getting to learn more about the company during the interview process.  Although I was disappointed to hear that I was not selected for the position, I do trust in your leadership when selecting the best fit candidate. If anything with this position changes or you feel I would be a suitable candidate for another role at your company, I would be happy to come back for additional consideration. I wish you and your team all the best in your search. #jobinterviewtips #jobinterviewquestions #jobhunt #careeradvice #jobinterviewprep #jobinterviewpreparation #careercoaching #careeradvice #careerchange #corporateamerica #rejectionfromajob #corporatelife #engineering #projectmanagement #supplychain #jobrejection #applyingtojobs #jobapplications #techjobs #remotework #worklife #workplaceboundaries #career #careertips #9-5 #corporatejob #professionalwomen #professionalmen #corporatelife #relatable #mentorship #dreamjob

desc: Would you take a helicopter from the airport instead of a taxi?? During my last visit to New York City, I got stuck in a taxi for over two hours from the airport to Manhattan 🤯🫣 plus it was almost $200 I heard about helicopters that can do it in under FIVE minutes, for around the same price, so I thought I would try it! My first ride was $195, and $50 bucks off (I know a code for first timers) so it was the same price as Uber, but a fraction of the time.  Carry on bag is free, checked costs a hefty extra.  The lounge came with free drinks, the 5-min ride had the most breathtaking views of the city, and I was shocked at how smooth and quick everything was 😍😍 This saved me a ton of time and I would do it again in a heartbeat, especially if my flight was coming in or departing around rush-hour. * * * * #helicopter #blade #travellife #avgeek  #nycviews #helicopterride #travelhacks #traveltips #nyctips

stickersText: ['Älä mene tänne Vietnamissa, mikäli sulla on ahtaanpaikankammo ja pelkäät skorpioneja!', 'Käytiin tutustumassa Cu Chi tunneleihin, joita Vietkong käytti Vietnamin sodassa. Tunnelit sijaitsee noin 1h ajomatkan päässä Vietnamin suurimmasta kaupungista Ho Chi Minh Citystä', 'Päästiin kulkemaan tunneleiden sisällä, niitä on levennetty turisteja varten ja siltikin tuntu ahtaalta', 'Jenna mahtui kulkemaan kyyryssä, mutta Juhon piti kontata kun on sen verran pitkä ', 'Tunneleissa ja viidakossa oli sodan aikana paljon rottia, käärmeitä, skorpioneja ja tulimuurahaisia', 'Tunneleissa tulee kuulemma  toisinaan vieläkin vastaan skorpioneja', 'Tiesitkö että amerikkalaiset polttivat valtaosan alueen viidakosta, jotta pääsivät kulkemaan paremmin alueella?', 'Meille esiteltiin myös Vietkongin sodassa käyttämiä ansoja ', 'Ansoja oli monenlaisia ja tämmöiseen astuneelle oli tiedossa pahimmillaan pitkä ja hidas kuolema', 'Tunneleita käytettiin yli kymmenen vuoden ajan ja ne kaivettiin käsin, yhteensä noin 250km useaan eri tasoon.', 'Täällä pääsi myös ampumaradalle ampumaan sodassa käytetyillä aseilla', 'Vaihtoehtoina oli mm. AK-47, M16, Colt 45, jne', 'Luodeista piti maksaa erikseen', 'Sitten mentiin ampumaradalle', 'Juho ampui AK-47:lla', 'Tämä oli suomalaiselle jotenkin erikoinen mahdollisuus, ei tiedetä että Suomessa ois tälläistä jonku nähtävyyden yhteydessä ', 'Voi kyllä rehellisesti sanoa ettei tuolla ois ite selvinny päivääkään 🥵😬', 'Paina ❤️ ja laita tili seurantaan!']

desc: From South Africa 🇿🇦 To Uruguay 🇺🇾  🤩Wow Can't believe it's been a year! Today exactly 1 year ago we climbed on a plane with only 7 suitcases and left South Africa 🇿🇦  (our home country) to Uruguay 🇺🇾 on a journey to live our dream lives!  It took us less than 2 years to achieve this goal!  All thanx to being able to earn online!  We wanted a different base we can call home and travel from! Uruguay was the best and easiest option for us to get residency!  It's a beautiful country, safe and clean and a tax haven!   We decided on Punta del Este which is the Gem 💎 of Uruguay!  We will be staying here 6 months out of the year and travel the other 6 months to other countries!  🤑None of this would be possible if it wasn't for the amazing opportunities online.  The ability to work form anywhere in the world from your smart phone for 2-4 hours a day,  making insane amounts of money still feels like a dream!  We were unhappy with our lifestyles! stickersText: ['Kathia de El Salvador 🇸🇻 ', '¡De cuando conseguí el trabajo remoto de mis sueños en Virtual Latinos!', 'Storytime', '¡De cuando conseguí el trabajo remoto de mis sueños en Virtual Latinos!', 'Antes de trabajar remoto trabajé para múltiples rubros en mi país 🇸🇻', 'Desde una ONG, pasando por el rubro farmacéutico (en la empresa familiar) hasta una multinacional de productos de consumo masivo ', 'En todos los anteriores JAMAS me sentí completamente llena con lo que hacía', '\U0001f979\U0001f972', 'O me llenaba lo que hacía pero el sueldo era muy poco ', 'Así que emprendí en algo que realmente amo💜🐶', '🐶🐶🐶🐶🐶', 'Pero, eso no era suficiente para mantenerme ', 'Solo era un extra 💸 ', '🔥 Necesitaba un boost \nen mi carrera 🔥', '💸 Y sobre TODO quería independizarme económicamente 💸 ', 'Pero viendo la realidad laboral de mi país me parecía IMPOSIBLE ', 'Siendo el salario mínimo de mi país 🇸🇻 de $360, jamas gané más de $800', 'Y aunque tengo preparación de una de las universidades “más prestigiosas” de El Salvador 🇸🇻 ', 'Eso no contaba a la hora de negociar mi salario \U0001f972', '💜 Un día estaba en Instagram y me salió un anuncio de VL 💜', 'Me pareció una súper opción para crecer profesionalmente, trabajar desde la comodidad de mi casa', 'y además de no sufrir el tráfico estresante de mi país 🙈', '(Sí sos de El Salvador o nos has visitado sabes de que estoy hablando)', '(Era mi primera vez que estaba en contacto con una plataforma así)', 'Cuando apliqué a VL estaba un poco escéptica ', 'Pero cada vez que avanzaba en el proceso', 'me daba cuenta de lo bien estructurados y organizados que estaban', '(Incluso hasta mejor que la multinacional que les conté anteriormente)', 'El equipo de VL me entrevistó cuando yo estaba en un viaje familiar ', 'Y en mi país perdí una oportunidad laboral por ese viaje 😭', 'Querían que empezara de inmediato y mi viaje estaba planeado y todo pagado desde hace meses 💸\U0001f90c🏽', 'Además que fue el viaje donde me comprometí \U0001f979', 'No me lo podía perder \U0001fae3', 'Y en ese momento estaba más estresada en encontrar un ingreso más alto \U0001f979', '(Se venía una boda y una casa que pagar) 😓', 'Después me entrevistó Ale quien es hoy mi jefa y vio algo en mi, ¡que en mi país no vieron! 💜', 'Ahora trabajo como Brand Strategist para Virtual Latinos 💜', 'Confían en mi y\noyen mis ideas 💡 ', '💜 Hoy puedo decir que soy feliz haciendo lo que hago, además de pertenecer a esta linda familia 💜 ', '💜 Tengo un sueldo que me ha permitido soñar en grande para mi futura familia y disfrutar en el proceso 💜', '💜 Definitivamente VL cambió mi vida💜', '🙏🏽', 'No esperes más para cambiar tu realidad', 'y aplica en el link de nuestra bio 💜', 'Te comparto mi historia porque esto te puede pasar a ti 💜', 'Aplicando ya a VL']

desc: I started my Etsy shop in March/April 2022. I was due with my second baby, coming in early May, and my goal was to have my Etsy shop up before I gave birth.  I figured to get sales; I would have to promote my shop on social media. So I set it up, planning to return to it a few months post-baby.  May baby was born. I got zero sales.  June, I wasn’t paying attention, but I got a few organic sales.  July, I realized I was getting a few sales here and there. I think I made $158 that month.  August, I dove back into it, hoping to make an extra $500 a month passively from my shop. I tweaked my product, bringing me to my first $1k. This video explains the strategy that I used: @Des | Selling Digital Products  In the last year, my shop has made over $45k in revenue. All from products I made essentially one time (with minor tweaks here and there), and I have never had to promote my shop 🤯 Here is what I wish I had known when I had started:@Des | Selling Digital Products  #figuringitoutonline #sellingcanvatemplates #workfromanywhere #etsypassiveincome #sellingonetsy #

desc: Did you know 3 million sellers joined Amazon since 2021? And guess what? Almost half of them are making between $1,000 to $25,000 each month. You might think it's just for the rich folks, but that's not true. With Amazon FBA, you don't have to be a wizard in market trends like crypto and stocks. You also don't have to worry about the headache of shipping like with dropshipping. Or even managing a mountain of inventory and a physical store like local businesses. And best of all, you don't need a mountain of money like you do in real estate. All you need is about 1,000 pounds and the right steps to start. This Sunday, I’m hosting a free Airbnb workshop teaching you step-by-step on how to get started. (I used this same blueprint to make multiple 6 figures from Amazon at 23 years old. Check out my profile description for more.) #jatznaran  #enterpreneur  #amazonseller  #onlinebusiness  #amazonfba  #sidehustle  #workfromanywhere  #financialfreedom  #entrepreneurlife

desc: Your denial is a reflection of you. When you’re not in proximity to $20k a month it seems so unrealistic it’s laughable, but when you hit 5k you think “Well I can do 7.” Then “I can do 10” “Okay let’s do 15” “Going for 20” and it all CLICKS.  There is no cap to making money online. The bar has been set so low in society that they make you believe that people don’t make 10k, 20k 30k a month. You internalize that narrative, and it makes it so that you can’t even begin to believe it for yourself. And because you can’t believe it for yourself, then you can’t believe it for others either.  I know people that make 80k a month online, while it’s something I still strive for, I know that it’s possible & I have no trouble believing it.  Don’t be the person who projects their own self doubt onto others. Especially people who are already there, because you aren’t hurting me, or them. We already got there. It’s you that needs to get there. I want you there. I can help! You don’t have to believe that I can help, but if you can get out of your own head, utilize my resources in my Stan store and change your life. I’ve helped over 700 people do it. desc: [Freelancing Life] Besides doing a 9 to 5 job, I also have some freelance jobs as my additional income. Doing a freelance job while also having a full-time job mengharuskan saya untuk mengorbankan beberapa hal, seperti waktu tidur yang akhirnya lebih sedikit, waktu weekend, dan kesenangan masa muda lainnya. Beberapa minggu ini saya coba mengubah pola kerja saya, dari yang sebelummya kerja sampai larut setelah selesai full-time, menjadi kerja lebih pagi sebelum full-time. I try to sleep as early as possible setelah selesai kerjaan full-time, kemudian bangun lebih pagi untuk ngerjain side project or freelance job. Tantangan untuk terus belajar hal baru seringkali datang dari freelance job and for me this is my chance to sharpen my skills. For me, selagi masih muda, selagi energi nya masih banyak dan otak nya masih kuat untuk belajar hal-hal baru, mengorbankan kesenangan-kesenangan jangka pendek bukanlah hal yang perlu disesali. I love doing my coding job, so it's not a big deal for me. #softwaredeveloper #softwareengineerlife #softwareengineer #coding #codinglife #freelance #flutterdeveloper #remotework #workfromhome #dayinmylife #dayinthelife #workfromanywhere
hashtagNames: softwaredeveloper, softwareengineerlife, softwareengineer, coding, codinglife, freelance, flutterdeveloper, remotework, workfromhome, dayinmylife, dayinthelife, workfromanywhere
